",["$r","p",null,{"children":["Depending on an object like this defeats the point of memoization. When a component re-renders, all of the code directly inside the component body runs again. ",["$r","strong",null,{"children":["The lines of code creating the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"searchOptions"}]," object will also run on every re-render."]}]," Since ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"searchOptions"}]," is a dependency of your ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"useMemo"}]," call, and it’s different every time, React knows the dependencies are different, and recalculate ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"searchItems"}]," every time."]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":["To fix this, you could memoize the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"searchOptions"}]," object ",["$r","em",null,{"children":"itself"}]," before passing it as a dependency:"]}],"
